node.title: Germany COVID-19 death toll passes 100,000 as fourth wave rages
node.description: Germany's outgoing Chancellor Angela Merkel urges her successor to impose new measures to slow the spread of the virus as the nation marks a grim milestone.

node.title: When will international travel in Queensland return to normal?
node.description: Airlines cannot commit to reinstating or establishing international flights in and out of Brisbane due to ongoing uncertainty about border closures, quarantine and COVID-19 testing requirements, travel industry advocates say.

node.title: Phil witnessed China tourism boom in Australia. But now that's over and many like him have moved on
node.description: China's new official report says the majority of its citizens choose to travel domestically, which poses 'great uncertainty' about when, and whether, Chinese tourists will return to Australia in pre-pandemic numbers.

node.title: Saving History With Sandbags: Climate Change Threatens the Smithsonian
node.description: Beneath the National Museum of American History, floodwaters are intruding into collection rooms, a consequence of a warming planet. A fix remains years away.

node.title: A native New Yorker wrangles a balloon in the Thanksgiving parade.
node.description: Decked in a white jumpsuit and blue smock with a Pikachu cartoon on it, George Gustines maneuvered the huge blowup cartoon character down New York’s streets on Thursday.

node.title: Nearly 70,000 Californians Without Power on Thanksgiving Amid High Winds
node.description: Thousands of additional Southern California residents could face power shutoffs throughout the day due to dangerous weather conditions.

node.title: Joy and relief for Black America after guilty verdict in Ahmaud Arbery killing
node.description: About 100 supporters of Ahmaud Arbery's family and Black activists broke into elated cheers and whoops outside the Georgia courthouse on Wednesday as the judge read the first verdict: "Guilty."

node.title: Unclear whether Medsafe to analyse vaccine data for kids over Christmas break
node.description: But experts say it's prudent to wait for more information before making a decision on vaccine approval for a population group where the chances of severe illness are slim.

node.title: Biden visits Coast Guard on Thanksgiving
node.description: President Biden and his family are spending Thanksgiving on Nantucket island.

node.title: EU Advises Member Countries to Not Enact Tighter COVID Restrictions, Over Travel Concerns
node.description: In hopes of saving free travel between the nation-bloc's 27 countries, the EU is recommending countries against implementing restrictions amid the latest surge.

node.title: 'They stop women from having dreams': Arezo is speaking out, something forbidden in her homeland
node.description: Exam pressure in Year 12 can be hard enough, but Hobart student Arezo Hami has had the added layer of negotiating help for Afghan family members coping with life under the Taliban.

node.title: How First Nations footballer Kyah Simon found her voice
node.description: The Indigenous Matilda only learned about the extent of her family history as an adult, but is now using her knowledge and the wider Black Lives Matter movement to speak out on issues of racism and discrimination.

node.title: Efat couldn't say goodbye to her family when she fled Kabul. Now she doesn't know if she'll see them again
node.description: Recently evacuated Afghans are pleading with the federal government to prioritise their families' visa applications because of their connections to Australia, amid concerns they could be targeted by the Taliban.

node.title: The world is asking 'Where is Peng Shuai?', but Chinese tennis fans don't even know she's missing
node.description: Even China's biggest tennis fans haven't heard about Peng Shuai's alleged disappearance, which is causing alarm among international tennis players and human rights groups.

node.title: 'I couldn't find a job to save my life': Prue spent three years looking for work before starting her own law firm
node.description: Australians with a disability have a much lower level of workforce participation than those without, with many locked out of job opportunities by prejudice. There's a growing body of evidence that suggests this is not just bad for them, but bad for business profits and the economy.

node.title: It’s been called 'the devil's machine’. Macquarie Bank used a more technical name for it
node.description: Internal documents show how Australia's largest investment bank took part in a controversial German tax scheme despite warnings of reputational damage and legal risk.

node.title: A new generation challenges Morrison amid a chaotic week full of revolts
node.description: Within the shambles, there has actually been one encouraging sign. We're seeing a new generation of Liberal moderates belatedly raise their voices, writes Michelle Grattan.

node.title: NASA moves ahead with December launch for Hubble successor
node.description: NASA cleared engineers to begin fueling the $10 billion James Webb Space Telescope for launch December 22.

node.title: ‘Licorice Pizza’ Review: California Dreaming and Scheming
node.description: In his latest movie, Paul Thomas Anderson returns to the San Fernando Valley for a shaggy 1970s romp about a self-important teenage boy and a memorable woman.

node.title: These slivers of carved mammoth tusk may be ancient jewellery — or something else entirely
node.description: A beautiful ivory artefact is the oldest example of decorated jewellery in Eurasia,  international archaeologists say. But could it be something even more intriguing?

node.title: Happiness is being able to afford a surprise vet bill

node.title: Schools can still expel LGBTQ+ kids. The Religious Discrimination Bill only makes it worse
node.description: The Religious Discrimination Bill, in its third iteration, does nothing to protect LGBTQ+ students and teachers. It allows more, not less, discrimination by religious schools.

node.title: Live music to return in a 'major way' next year after summer shortage, peak body says

node.title: 'Tis the season for those tricky vaccine convos with your family. Here's how to go about it

node.title: Solomon Islands Prime Minister blames foreign powers for civil unrest that prompted call to Australia for help

node.title: Countdown to Softball World Cup starts again

node.title: Survey shows extent of Covid-19 impact on south Westland

node.title: With ‘Encanto,’ Stephanie Beatriz Finds Yet Another Voice

node.title: Animal Shelter Overwhelmed After Rescuing 42 Cats From One Home: 'I Started to Cry'

node.title: Over One-Quarter of Texas Parents Say They Won't Vaccinate Their Child Against COVID: Poll
node.description: The survey comes after the CDC recommended earlier this month that children ages 5 to 11 should receive Pfizer's pediatric COVID-19 vaccine.
